{"title":"IPH 533 - Who is on the Lord’s side?","verses":[{"lines":["Who is on the Lord’s side?","Who will serve the King?","Who will be His helpers,"," other lives to bring?","\fWho will leave the world’s side?"," Who will face the foe?"," Who is on the Lord’s side?"," Who for Him will go?","\f By Your call of mercy,"," by Your grace alone,","we are on the Lord’s side,"," Saviour, all Your own."]},{"lines":["\f Jesus, You have bought us,"," not with gold or gem,","but with Your own life-blood,"," for Your diadem.","\fWith Your blessing filling"," all who come in need,","You have made us willing,"," made us free indeed.","\fBy Your great redemption,"," by Your grace alone,","we are on the Lord’s side,"," Saviour, all Your own."]},{"lines":["\fFierce may be the conflict,"," strong may be the foe;"," but the King’s own army"," none can overthrow.","\fRound His standard ranging,"," victory is secure;"," for His truth unchanging"," makes the triumph sure.","\f Joyfully enlisting,"," by Your grace alone,","we are on the Lord’s side"," Saviour, all Your own."]},{"lines":["\f Chosen to be soldiers"," in a hostile land,","chosen, called and faithful,"," for our Captain’s band.","\f In His service royal"," let us not grow cold;"," let us then be loyal,","steadfast, true and bold.","\f Master, You will keep us"," by Your grace alone,"," always on the Lord’s side,"," Saviour, all Your own."]}],"chorus":"","CCLI":"Frances Ridley Havergal, 1836-1879\nAdapted Compilers of Praise! 2000 CCLI 128675\n"}